From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thomas Lamprecht <t.lamprecht@proxmox.com>
Date: Fri, 03 Jul 2026 21:04:40 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "drm/amd/display: Add Idle state manager(ISM)"

This reverts the Ubuntu SAUCE cherry-pick 707d6e61c341 (upstream AMD
commit 754003486c3c), which added the Idle State Manager (ISM).

On amdgpu device unbind, for example when handing a GPU to vfio-pci for
PCIe passthrough, dm_hw_fini() -> amdgpu_dm_fini() frees adev->dm.dc via
dc_destroy() without first cancelling the ISM delayed work. A pending
sso_delayed_work timer, armed while the display went idle during
teardown, then fires and calls dc_allow_idle_optimizations() on the
now-NULL dc, dereferencing it:

  BUG: kernel NULL pointer dereference, address: 00000000000000b4
  RIP: dc_allow_idle_optimizations_internal+0x1f [amdgpu]
   dm_ism_commit_idle_optimization_state+0xee [amdgpu]
   amdgpu_dm_ism_commit_event+0x104 [amdgpu]
   dm_ism_sso_delayed_work_func+0x40 [amdgpu]

As the worker dies holding dm->dc_lock, the triggering VM start task
hangs indefinitely. Reported for a Radeon RX 9070 XT passed through to a
guest, seen only since 7.0.14 pulled in the ISM feature.

ISM rate-limits IPS, PSR and Replay idle optimizations, which benefit
mainly APUs and internal eDP panels; a discrete GPU driving external
displays on a hypervisor host gains nothing from it. Drop it until a fix
that stops the ISM timers before dc teardown lands upstream.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Lamprecht <t.lamprecht@proxmox.com>
